## Secrets & Credentials
- NEVER hardcode API keys, passwords, tokens, or connection strings in any file.
- ALWAYS fetch secrets from HashiCorp Vault at: https://45.88.223.83:31313
- Vault secret path for all project secrets: cubbyhole/internal-erp/db
- Known Vault keys: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, DIRECTUS_ADMIN_EMAIL, DIRECTUS_PASSWORD, DIRECTUS_TOKEN, DIRECTUS_KEY, DIRECTUS_SECRET, BS4_DEV_PASSWORD
- If you need a secret, say "I need [secret_name] from Vault" and use the vault MCP tool.
- NEVER write a secret to a log, console output, or comment.

## Database (PostgreSQL via Directus)
- ALWAYS use the Directus SDK (@directus/sdk) for CRUD operations in application code.
- Directus URL: https://bs4.expertflow.com (v11.12.0, MCP enabled)
- Use the directus MCP to inspect collections, fields, and permissions before coding.
- NEVER bypass Directus permissions by going directly to PostgreSQL in app code.
- PostgreSQL port 5432 is NOT publicly exposed - all DB access goes through Directus API.
- Only use raw SQL via the postgresql MCP for schema inspection, migrations, and reporting.
- Before writing any DB query, check the schema via the postgresql MCP first.

## Key ERP Collections (bs4.expertflow.com)
- Finance: Account, Accruals, Allocation, BankStatement, Invoice, Journal, Transaction, Currency, CurrencyExchange
- HR: Employee, Leaves, Seniority, Designation, department, EmployeePersonalInfo
- CRM: Contact, Deal, Quotes, LegalEntity, Company, QuoteLineItems
- Projects: Project, Task, TimeEntry, InternalCost, ProfitCenter
- Support: tickets, ticket_updates, sla_definitions
- Products: product_catalogue, ProductDependencies
- Total: 75 collections | Users: 11 | Roles: Administrator, HRandFinance, SSO JIT (minimal)

## BMAD Method (v6.2.0)
- Project name: BMADMonorepoEFInternalTools
- BMAD root: _bmad/ (agents, workflows, config)
- BMAD output: _bmad-output/ (planning-artifacts/, implementation-artifacts/)
- Project knowledge: docs/ (governance.md, legal-entity-insights.md)
- Read _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ BEFORE writing any new feature code.
- Read _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/ BEFORE implementing any story.
- Read docs/ for governance and architectural decisions.
- Update _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/ when completing a story.
- BMAD agents available: analyst, architect, dev, pm, qa, sm, ux-designer, tech-writer
- BMAD workflows: create-prd, create-architecture, create-epics-and-stories, dev-story, sprint-planning, sprint-status, retrospective, document-project, generate-project-context, qa-generate-e2e-tests, quick-flow

## Project Structure
- projects/internal-erp/directus/ - Directus configuration, extensions, scripts, SQL
- projects/internal-erp/directus/extensions/ - Custom Directus extensions (bank-import, cash-flow-api, finance-dashboard, rls-user-context)
- projects/internal-erp/directus/scripts/ - Migration and configuration scripts
- projects/internal-erp/directus/docs/sql/ - SQL migrations and diagnostics
- projects/internal-erp/bank-import/ - Python bank statement parser (UBS, generic CSV)
- projects/internal-erp/finance-streamlit/ - Finance dashboard (Python/Streamlit)
- projects/internal-erp/expense-api/ - Expense API (Node.js, GCP Cloud Run)
- projects/internal-erp/google-apps-script/ - Google Apps Script integrations

## Code Quality & Linting
- ALWAYS run the lint MCP check before raising a PR.
- ESLint must pass with zero errors before any commit.
- Gherkin/Cucumber feature files must exist for all new user-facing features.
- Run requirement-linter against _bmad-output/planning-artifacts before starting any new feature.

## Documentation
- Read _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ BEFORE writing any new feature code.
- Read _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/ BEFORE implementing any API endpoint or schema change.
- Update _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/ when you change an API contract or database schema.
- Key planning docs: prd-ExpertflowInternalERP-2026-03-16.md, architecture-BMADMonorepoEFInternalTools-2026-03-15.md, epics-ExpertflowInternalERP-2026-03-16.md

## Testing
- Use the playwright MCP to write and run end-to-end tests for all UI changes.
- Tests must pass before a PR is raised.
- Write tests ALONGSIDE the feature code, not after.
- E2E test target: https://bs4.expertflow.com

## LLM Model Selection
- Use Gemini 2.5 Pro for: initial architecture, large context tasks (>100k tokens).
- Use Claude Sonnet for: active coding, complex logic, refactoring.
- Use Gemini 2.5 Flash for: unit tests, documentation strings, simple boilerplate.

## GCP & Infrastructure
- Target platform: GCP (Cloud Run, Firebase, PostgreSQL, Docker).
- GCP project: expertflowerp, region: us-central1
- Use Angular/Material, Bootstrap, Tailwind, Ngx-charts - NOT React/Vite/Shadcn.
- Directus runs on GCP VM (bs4.expertflow.com) via Docker Compose.
- See projects/internal-erp/directus/docker-compose.yml for container config.

## Git & SAFe
- Every AI-generated code change must pass linting and SpecKit validation (Definition of Done).
- Commit messages must reference the Jira ticket number.
- Never push directly to main - always raise a PR.

## Governance (docs/governance.md)
- All architectural decisions must include a Licensing Lever Analysis.
- Prefer open-source/portable frameworks (self-hosted PostgreSQL over proprietary NoSQL).
- Security (RBAC/RLS) must be managed at the API/Backend layer, never solely in the Frontend.
- Direct database access must be restricted via Directus to prevent AI-assisted dev from bypassing security.
